Package org.neo4j.storageengine.api

Interface StorageCursor

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    StorageEntityCursor, StorageEntityScanCursor<S>, StorageNodeCursor, StoragePropertyCursor, StorageRelationshipCursor, StorageRelationshipScanCursor, StorageRelationshipTraversalCursor
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    RecordNodeCursor, RecordPropertyCursor, RecordRelationshipCursor, RecordRelationshipScanCursor, RecordRelationshipTraversalCursor
    public interface StorageCursor
extends AutoCloseable
    Base interface for a cursor accessing and reading data as part of StorageReader.

    • Method Detail

      • next

        boolean next()
        Positions this cursor and reads the next item that it has been designated to read.
        Returns:
        true if the item was read and in use, otherwise false.

      • reset

        void reset()
        Resets state in this cursor so that calls to next() will not return true anymore. After this point this cursor can still be used, after initializing it with any of the cursor-specific initialization method.

      • setTracer

        default void setTracer​(ReadTracer tracer)

      • removeTracer

        default void removeTracer()

      • setForceLoad

        void setForceLoad()
        Force loading of the data and ignore errors, even when the datums are unavailable (like not-in-use records) or cannot be properly loaded or decoded. This must ONLY be used by the consistency checker. This method must be called after any cursor initializing call, such as scan, single, or init, and before any call to next(). A call to reset() will undo this call.

      • close

        void close()
        Closes and releases resources allocated by this cursor so that it cannot be initialized or used again after this call.
        Specified by:
        close in interface AutoCloseable
